    "body": "## User visual authority\n\nAfter PR #257 merged to `main` `a8b86aeaf6d36b18dffb0addab97a74b42cae7c9`, the user visually rechecked the actual game and supplied a screenshot proving both duplicate stat-toast classes still remained, including a standalone money icon toast directly below the permanent money stat anchor. The user also required simultaneous stat toasts to combine rather than overlap, questioned the Alpha-facing term `контраргумент`, and reported visible `вброс` leakage in Boomer and Millennial. Stage 6 remains NOT COMPLETE.\n\n## Final Stage 6 canon recheck\n\nThe final Stage 6 contract is one unchanged game with four full language personas across visible UI/system surfaces. Mechanics, economy, REP semantics, battle outcomes, NPC behavior, state and persistence must remain identical.\n\nCurrent UI also contradicted profile canon:\n- final Zoomer canon explicitly forbids fake youth slang / meme performance, while the prior repair still used `Вброс`, `Ответка`, `Заслать`, `Отвали`, `Свалить`, `репа`, `лут`, etc.;\n- Alpha is a terse delta over Zoomer, but must preserve meaning. Cryptic `Атк` and formal `контраргумент` are not acceptable simplification;\n- Boomer and Millennial must not leak Zoomer-only presentation terms such as `Вброс` / `Ответка`.\n\n## Root cause\n\nThe base UI exposes two independent stat-toast paths:\n1. `UI.emitStatDelta()` creates a fresh unique `.statToast--delta` node per change.\n2. `UI.showStatToast()` separately creates normal stat toasts for system/economy notifications.\n\nThe legacy de-dup logic explicitly skips delta toasts, so late icon stripping could never solve overlap. Respect flow also emits separate money and target-reputation messages, which can visually stack even though they belong to one action.\n\n## Repair v4\n\nThe final Stage 6 presentation module now becomes the single runtime owner of both stat-toast APIs before gameplay interaction:\n- both `UI.showStatToast` and `UI.emitStatDelta` feed one coalescing accumulator;\n- simultaneous money/REP/influence/win changes render in one toast block;\n- nearby updates reuse/merge into the active block instead of stacking DOM nodes;\n- legacy `.statToast--delta` / `statToast_*` nodes are neutralized;\n- stat icons are not repeated inside the toast because the permanent anchors already show them;\n- authoritative numeric deltas win over duplicate semantic notifications, preventing double-counting;\n- target reputation is kept semantically distinct from the player's REP. Example respect result:\n  - Millennial: `Баланс: −1 · Репутация цели: +1`\n  - Zoomer: `−1 к балансу · Цели +1 к репутации`\n  - Alpha: `Деньги −1 / Цель: репутация +1`\n  - Boomer: `Баланс уменьшился на 1. У цели репутация выросла на 1.`\n\n## Final visible terminology\n\nPlayer-facing `Вброс`, `Ответка`, `контраргумент`, cryptic `Атк`, and the prior fake-Zoomer slang are removed/routed on controlled UI surfaces while internal mechanic ids remain untouched.\n\nExamples:\n- Millennial: `Аргумент` / `Ответ`, neutral complete labels.\n- Zoomer: shorter/direct wording without fake slang or meme voice.\n- Alpha: `Ход` / `Ответ`, minimal but understandable.\n- Boomer: `Аргумент` / `Ответ`, fuller explanatory wording.\n\nThe module also canonicalizes known legacy Zoomer system phrases such as `Кошелёк в нуле 💀`, `Лут прилетел`, `Репа просела`, etc. into the accepted final Zoomer lane.\n\n## Safety\n\n- PR #245 frozen Alpha keys remain untouched and fail-closed in smoke.\n- No gameplay, economy, prices, battle rules, NPC behavior, handlers, state, persistence, or outcomes changed.\n- Current source and docs presentation mirrors are byte-identical.\n\n## Runtime gate\n\n`Game.__DEV.smokeStage6FinalVisualToneRepairOnce()` now checks:\n- Alpha frozen-copy preservation;\n- four distinct profile previews;\n- no visible `Вброс` / `Ответка` leakage in profile previews;\n- no prior fake Zoomer slang in the final Zoomer preview;\n- no `контраргумент` / `Атк` in Alpha preview;\n- both stat-toast public APIs owned by the single v4 pipeline;\n- no legacy delta nodes at install/runtime gate;\n- exact combined-toast preview for all four profiles;\n- target-REP text is not parsed as the player's own REP delta;\n- profile/system/observer/watcher hooks installed.\n\nAutomated PASS is diagnostic only. Stage 6 remains NOT COMPLETE until the user visually accepts the deployed result.\n\n## Exact diff\n\nBase: `a8b86aeaf6d36b18dffb0addab97a74b42cae7c9`\n\nExactly four paths:\n- `AsyncScene/Web/index.html`\n- `docs/index.html`\n- `AsyncScene/Web/ui/ui-profile-visual-tone-repair.js`\n- `docs/ui/ui-profile-visual-tone-repair.js`\n\nPresentation mirrors: `df69cc0ac3e7e3899955d0144cb06e5d0dfa6347`.\nIndex mirrors: `1b97ea0fc63374fe150782796674f9618bf42a90`.\nEach index changes exactly one script cache-bust line to `stage6_final_presentation_v4_20260723a`.",
